author: Lisa Beilfuss
title: SunTrust’s Adjusted Earnings Top Expectations
text:
SunTrust Banks Inc. said its profit fell in its latest quarter because of a tax benefit that lifted the comparable quarter’s earnings. On an adjusted basis, the regional lender reported 23% profit growth and topped expectations.
The bank reported a profit of $537 million, down from $576 million a year earlier. On a per-share basis, earnings fell to $1 from $1.06. Excluding one-time items, including a tax benefit, per-share profit...
